<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n34005d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n34" href="#n34005d">N34 (VI.B.27)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n34all.htm#n34005d"> 5(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> bishop celibacy / priest monogamy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">All ministers of Christ must be regularly called and appointed to their office, and are consecrated <i>by the sacrament of orders</i>. Bishops must be unmarried,</i> and <font size="-1">PRIESTS AND DEACONS MUST NOT CONTRACT A SECOND MARRIAGE</font>. <small> &ldquo;ORTHODOX EASTERN CHURCH&rdquo; <a name="EBOEC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBOEC"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 336 [Comparison of Orthodox, Roman and Protestant doctrine [NOTE. Small capitals denote differences of the Greek Orthodox doctrine from Roman Catholic, italics differences from Protestant doctrines.]]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
